{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "869e7286-b605-4ff3-b215-35967838100e",
    "name": "blacklist_postman_collection",
    "description": "# Documentación de Endpoints Blacklist\n\n## Seguridad\nTodas las rutas requieren el header:\n\n    Authorization: Bearer fixedtoken\n\n## Endpoints principales\n\n### 1. Obtener lista de emails en blacklist\n- **GET /blacklists**\n- Devuelve todos los emails en la blacklist.\n\n### 2. Buscar email en blacklist\n- **GET /blacklists/<email>**\n- Devuelve si el email está en blacklist y el motivo.\n\n### 3. Crear email en blacklist\n- **POST /blacklists**\n- Cuerpo (JSON):\n    {\n        \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n        \"app_uuid\": \"uuid-app\",\n        \"blocked_reason\": \"motivo opcional\"\n    }\n- Respuesta: email registrado en blacklist.\n\n### 4. Ejemplo de uso con curl\n\nPOST:\n    curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/blacklists/ -H 'Authorization: Bearer fixedtoken' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"email": "test@example.com", "app_uuid": "123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000", "blocked_reason": "spam"}'\n\nGET:\n    curl -X GET http://localhost:5000/blacklists/test@example.com -H 'Authorization: Bearer fixedtoken'\n\nPara más detalles, consulta el README del proyecto.\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "33854284"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Test-trafico-estrategia",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Lista de Emails",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const code = pm.response.code;\r",
                  "const previous = pm.collectionVariables.get(\"previous_code\");\r",
                  "\r",
                  "let total = Number(pm.collectionVariables.get(\"total\") || 0);\r",
                  "let ok = Number(pm.collectionVariables.get(\"ok\") || 0);\r",
                  "let fail = Number(pm.collectionVariables.get(\"fail\") || 0);\r",
                  "\r",
                  "total += 1;\r",
                  "\r",
                  "if (code >= 200 && code < 300) {\r",
                  "    ok += 1;\r",
                  "} else {\r",
                  "    fail += 1;\r",
                  "}\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"total\", total);\r",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"ok\", ok);\r",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"fail\", fail);\r",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"previous_code\", code);\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Respuesta aceptada para prueba de despliegue\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect([200, 500, 502, 503, 504]).to.include(code);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "if (previous && Number(previous) !== code) {\r",
                  "    console.log(`Cambio detectado: ${previous} -> ${code}`);\r",
                  "}\r",
                  "\r",
                  "console.log(\"Iteración:\", total);\r",
                  "console.log(\"HTTP:\", code);\r",
                  "console.log(\"OK acumulados:\", ok);\r",
                  "console.log(\"FAIL acumulados:\", fail);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://cd-beanstalk-app.us-east-1.elasticbeanstalk.com/blacklists",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "cd-beanstalk-app",
                "us-east-1",
                "elasticbeanstalk",
                "com"
              ],
              "path": [
                "blacklists"
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
